{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 10:47:30.134451", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and topology\\n- Data center Clos (fat-tree) with EBGP: super-spine (AS 65000), spines per pod (expected AS 65100 and 65101), leaves (AS 65200 and 65201), hosts on 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24.\\n- Devices: super_spine_router_0; spines: spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1; leaves: leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1; hosts: pc_0_0, pc_0_1.\\n\\nEnd-to-end reachability (data plane)\\n- Host-to-host pings are successful with 0% loss and low RTT:\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: RTT avg 3.22 ms, 0% loss.\\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: RTT avg 2.06 ms, 0% loss.\\n- Leaf routing tables:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.8 (to spine_router_0_1).\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.10 (to spine_router_0_1).\\n- Conclusion: End-to-end connectivity is currently working via spine_router_0_1.\\n\\nControl-plane status (BGP)\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000):\\n  - Established with spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101) and receiving both /24s.\\n  - Neighbor to 172.16.0.1 (expected AS 65100) is Active (not established).\\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101):\\n  - Established with super_spine_router_0, leaf_router_0_0, and leaf_router_0_1.\\n  - Routing table carries both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 via its leaf peers.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) and leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201):\\n  - Both are Established to spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101) with 1 prefix received.\\n  - Both are not up to spine_router_0_0: neighbors to 172.16.0.4/172.16.0.6 (expected AS 65100) are in Active.\\n- spine_router_0_0:\\n  - All BGP neighbors (super spine and both leaves) are Idle with “Notification received (OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS)”.\\n  - BGP RIB empty; only connected 172.16.0.x routes in the routing table.\\n\\nConfiguration findings\\n- super_spine_router_0 is configured to peer with 172.16.0.1 remote-as 65100 (for spine_router_0_0).\\n- leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 are configured to peer to 172.16.0.4/172.16.0.6 with remote-as 65100 (for spine_router_0_0).\\n- spine_router_0_0 running config shows:\\n  - router bgp 65700 (local AS 65700)\\n  - Neighbors defined to super-spine (172.16.0.0) and leaves (172.16.0.5, 172.16.0.7) but with the wrong local AS.\\n- This local AS (65700) does not match the expected AS (65100), triggering OPEN Message Error/Bad Peer AS on all its EBGP neighbors.\\n\\nAssessment and anomalies\\n- Anomaly detected: spine_router_0_0 has a misconfigured local BGP AS (65700 instead of 65100).\\n- Impact:\\n  - All BGP adjacencies to spine_router_0_0 are down.\\n  - Super-spine and leaves rely solely on spine_router_0_1 for inter-pod reachability.\\n  - Network is operational for current hosts but degraded: loss of redundancy and ECMP/load-sharing; single point of failure on spine_router_0_1.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty device: spine_router_0_0.\\n- Symptom localization: BGP state Idle to all peers; explicit BGP OPEN error “Bad Peer AS”.\\n- Corroborated by neighbor configurations on super_spine_router_0 and both leaves expecting AS 65100.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Misconfiguration on spine_router_0_0: local BGP AS set to 65700 instead of 65100, causing EBGP session failures with all intended neighbors., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='d1c27fb9-7865-411b-acbf-1513dad60896'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
